original: Lundquist, Per Pontus David, tandläkare, Göteborg, f. 6/8/94 i Södertälje av sjökapt. Herman L. o. Anna Palm. — Studiex. v. Gbgs^ latin 26, Cand. med. dent. i Marburg an der Lahn, Tyskl., 28, tysk tandl. i Königsberg 30, sv. tandl. 31. Prakt, i Gbg sed. 31.
translated: Lundquist, Per Pontus David, dentist, Gothenburg, born on August 6, 1894 in Södertälje to sea captain Herman L. and Anna Palm. — Completed his studies at Gothenburg Latin School in 1926, received his degree in dentistry from Marburg an der Lahn, Germany in 1928, became a German dentist in Königsberg in 1930, and a Swedish dentist in 1931. He has been practicing in Gothenburg since 1931.
